status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"ngs1","text":"Make sure waste to be autoclaved is in a biohazard bag (no more than 3/4 full) and place in autoclavable container.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8r3g1","text":"Wrap 2 Steam Migrating Integrator Strips together with autoclave tape and a piece of string and place in the middle of the bag of waste to be autoclaved with the piece of string hanging out of the bag so that the strips are easily retrieved after autoclave cycle is finished","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dc02c","text":"Tape string with autoclave tape to an AccuFast Biological Indicator (BI) and place in the middle of the bag of waste to be autoclaved with the piece of string hanging out of the bag so that the BI is easily retrieved after autoclave cycle is finished.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2pdgj","text":"Close the door with foot peddle and select Cycle 4 from the cycle menu and select 'Start Cycle.'","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7kvfa","text":"Add 1 liter of water to the bag and loosely close with autoclave tape leaving about a 2-finger space opening and load from door in room P209.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a2jb2","text":"When load is finished, open door with caution as steam can be released from the doorway and using appropriate PPE (temperature resistant gloves, lab coat, and goggles) unload the tray containing the bag.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"500il","text":"Observe autoclave tape color and record results (color change - yes or no). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4oara","text":"Remove and read the steam strips and record results.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bv7p2","text":"Remove BI and crack open glass ampule using the indicated slot in the incubator (L202) and incubate at 60°C for 10 hours. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"81suk","text":"If load has passed sterilization then it can be placed in a black trash bag and taken out to the trash. If load has not passed then it needs to be reautoclaved until it passes sterilization. Please see section on trouble shooting should this occur.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1hmt3","text":"In the case where BI and the steam strip results conflict, defer to the BI results as they are considered more accurate and consistent. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ed8em","text":"Place all media in autoclavable trays and make sure to not overload autoclave with media like stacking trays on top of each other (only one layer thick) or putting media bottles too close to each other (make sure they are not touching with at least a finger width or two apart)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"be1q","text":"Blue color indicates 'Pass' while yellow color indicates 'Fail.'","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b91su","text":"Blue in the 'Pass' window indicates 'Pass' otherwise it is considering 'Fail.'","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"emoi3","text":"If one steam strip fails and one strip passes, record as 'Pass.'","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
